3
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:16,560
Well, good evening everybody.

4
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,800
I'm glad to see you back, all of you.

5
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,560
So nice to have such a large class.

6
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:28,120
The last time we discussed the influence of electric and

7
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:32,680
magnetic fields on charged particles.

8
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:33,480
We know what they do.

9
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:34,820
We know what electric and

10
00:00:34,820 --> 00:00:36,160
magnetic fields do on charged particles.

11
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:39,240
They push them around, they pull them, they exert forces.

12
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:45,040
In fact, we even wrote some equations.

13
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:47,560
Let's write down the basic equation.

14
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:50,210
The basic equation is that the

15
00:00:50,210 --> 00:00:52,860
force on a charged particle, F,

16
00:00:52,860 --> 00:00:56,400
is equal to the electric charge of the charged particle.

17
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:57,760
Why is that there?

18
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:00,660
That's there because if the charged particle wasn't charged,

19
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:02,440
if it didn't have any charge,

20
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:04,220
there would be no force on it.

21
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:08,240
And then that gets multiplied by the electric field.

22
00:01:09,980 --> 00:01:11,440
Let's just call it the electric field.

23
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:17,840
Plus something that depends on the magnetic field.

24
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,760
And the thing that depends on

25
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:21,680
the magnetic field is the cross product

26
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:24,759
of the velocity with the magnetic field.

27
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:32,180
That's the basic influence of electric

28
00:01:32,180 --> 00:01:36,600
and magnetic fields on charged particles

29
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:37,530
is to exert forces on them

30
00:01:37,530 --> 00:01:38,460
to push them and pull them around

31
00:01:38,460 --> 00:01:42,020
and so forth.

32
00:01:42,020 --> 00:01:44,900
The missing piece, thus far, is what

33
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:47,780
is it that determines the electric and

34
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:49,620
magnetic fields in space?

35
00:01:49,620 --> 00:01:51,160
What is it that determines

36
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:52,700
whether there's a electromagnetic wave?

37
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:54,280
What is it that determines if a

38
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,860
electric charge field can create a electric change?

39
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:56,760
What is it that determines what matters to you?

40
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,440
And that's the final question.

41
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:57,590
There's lots, there's lots to be solving

42
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:57,740
in Make it, but hear me out please,

43
00:01:57,740 --> 00:02:01,240
produces an electric field and so forth, what

44
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:04,740
are the equations which govern the fields themselves?

45
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:07,740
Those equations are called Maxwell's equations, and those

46
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:10,740
are the equations we want to discuss this evening.

47
00:02:10,740 --> 00:02:13,240
They're the equations which tell

48
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,740
you how charged particles affect fields.

49
00:02:15,740 --> 00:02:18,240
Here is the equation which

50
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:20,740
says how fields affect charged particles.

51
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:22,740
The other half of the coin

52
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:24,740
is how charged particles affect fields.

53
00:02:24,740 --> 00:02:28,740
Why is it necessary that charged particles affect fields?

54
00:02:28,740 --> 00:02:31,740
Well, it's a kind of action and reaction thing.

55
00:02:31,740 --> 00:02:35,240
If electric and magnetic fields can

56
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:38,740
influence particles, what does that mean?

57
00:02:38,740 --> 00:02:42,240
It means an electromagnetic wave can come, hit a charged

58
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:45,740
particle, and send it off flying off in some other direction.

59
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:48,740
It can add energy to the charged particle.

60
00:02:48,740 --> 00:02:51,240
Well, if an electric field can

61
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:53,740
add energy to a charged particle,

62
00:02:53,740 --> 00:02:54,740
then it had done the same thing.

63
00:02:54,740 --> 00:02:57,740
It better be that a charged particle

64
00:02:57,740 --> 00:03:00,740
can suck energy out of an electric field.

65
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:02,740
Otherwise, energy wouldn't be conserved.

66
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:04,740
So it stands to reason, it's

67
00:03:04,740 --> 00:03:06,740
a kind of action and reaction thing,

68
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:09,240
that if electric and magnetic fields

69
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,740
can do things to particles, charged particles,

70
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:15,740
then charged particles, charged currents, electric charges, had better

71
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:19,740
be able to do things to electric and magnetic fields.

72
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:22,740
So that's the topic for tonight.

73
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:23,740
But as always in this course,

74
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:28,740
the basic question is whether the laws of physics,

75
00:03:28,740 --> 00:03:30,740
and in this case the laws

76
00:03:30,740 --> 00:03:32,740
of the electric and magnetic field,

77
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:35,740
are the same in all reference frames.

78
00:03:35,740 --> 00:03:37,740
That's the thing we've been concentrating

79
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:39,740
on in the study of relativity,

80
00:03:39,740 --> 00:03:42,740
is the idea that the basic laws of

81
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:45,740
physics are the same in all reference frames.

82
00:03:45,740 --> 00:03:47,740
Now, one of the things, we're going

83
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:49,740
to write down Maxwell's equations in a moment,

84
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:52,740
but one of the basic things that,

85
00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:57,740
we learned,

86
00:03:57,740 --> 00:04:01,740
by, well, let me go back a step.

87
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:04,740
One of the basic questions has to do with light.

88
00:04:04,740 --> 00:04:07,740
All of relativity theory had to do with light.

89
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:10,740
If Maxwell's equations are the theory of light,

90
00:04:10,740 --> 00:04:12,740
and Maxwell's equations tell you that

91
00:04:12,740 --> 00:04:14,740
light moves with the speed of light,

92
00:04:14,740 --> 00:04:16,740
and Maxwell's equations are the

93
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:18,740
same in every reference frame,

94
00:04:18,740 --> 00:04:20,740
it stands to reason,

95
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:22,740
that light will move with the

96
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:24,740
speed of light in every reference frame.

97
00:04:24,740 --> 00:04:26,740
This was precisely the puzzle

98
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:28,740
that Einstein wrestled with so hard.

99
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:32,740
How is it possible to get a description of nature

100
00:04:32,740 --> 00:04:34,740
in which light moves with the

101
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:36,740
same velocity in every frame of reference?

102
00:04:36,740 --> 00:04:40,740
That, the thing which ensures that,

103
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:43,240
is that the laws of physics

104
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,740
are the same in every reference frame,

105
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:48,740
and in past lectures we saw that what that meant,

106
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:49,740
is that the,

107
00:04:49,740 --> 00:04:53,740
equations of physics should be expressed,

108
00:04:53,740 --> 00:04:54,740
in terms of,

109
00:04:54,740 --> 00:04:58,740
quantities which have definite transformation laws,

110
00:04:58,740 --> 00:05:00,740
when you go from frame to frame.

111
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:02,740
That means scalars,

112
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:03,740
that don't change,

113
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:04,740
it means vectors,

114
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,740
four vectors,

115
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:08,740
it means tensors,

116
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:10,240
and it means all the

117
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,740
things that we discussed last time,

118
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:13,740
when we discussed the transformation properties,

119
00:05:13,740 --> 00:05:16,740
of the various things in physics.

120
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:18,740
Let me just remind you,

121
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:20,740
what this equation looks like,

122
00:05:20,740 --> 00:05:22,740
if it's expressed in a covariant form,

123
00:05:22,740 --> 00:05:24,740
in a form which is

124
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:26,740
the same in every reference frame.

125
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:31,740
It looks,

126
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:34,740
like,

127
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:36,740
an expression,

128
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:38,740
involving not electric and magnetic fields,

129
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:41,740
well yes, electric and magnetic fields,

130
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:42,740
but a tensor,

131
00:05:42,740 --> 00:05:43,740
a field tensor,

132
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:45,240
and I'll remind you in a

133
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,740
little while what that field tensor is,

134
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:47,740
but,

135
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:50,740
it's an anti-symmetric field tensor,

136
00:05:50,740 --> 00:05:52,740
which is built up out

137
00:05:52,740 --> 00:05:54,740
of the electric and magnetic fields,

138
00:05:54,740 --> 00:05:55,740
and it's multiplied,

139
00:05:55,740 --> 00:05:59,740
by the four vector of velocity,

140
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:01,740
this is the,

141
00:06:01,740 --> 00:06:04,740
mu component of the force.

142
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:06,740
The mu component of the force

143
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:08,740
is written in terms of a,

144
00:06:08,740 --> 00:06:10,740
four by four,

145
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,740
anti-symmetric tensor,

146
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:15,740
whose transformation properties we know,

147
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:17,740
and the four vector of velocity,

148
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:21,740
in this form,

149
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:23,740
the Lorentz force law,

150
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:24,740
is written in a form,

151
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:28,740
which is manifestly the same in every reference frame.

152
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:30,740
So, that's our goal,

153
00:06:30,740 --> 00:06:32,740
is to write all of the laws of physics,

154
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:34,740
in particular the Maxwell equations today,

155
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:36,740
in a form,

156
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:38,740
which is the same in every reference frame,

157
00:06:38,740 --> 00:06:41,240
which means writing it in terms

158
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,740
of vectors and tensors and so forth.

159
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,740
Now, let's just talk for a little bit,

160
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:46,740
before we get into it,

161
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:47,740
deeply,

162
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:49,740
let's talk about the kind of effects,

163
00:06:49,740 --> 00:06:52,740
that charges have on electric and magnetic fields.

164
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:55,740
Not that electric and magnetic fields have on charges,

165
00:06:55,740 --> 00:06:58,740
but that charges have on electric and magnetic fields.

166
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:00,740
Well, first of all,

167
00:07:00,740 --> 00:07:03,740
we know that if we have an electric charge,

168
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:05,740
we'll call an electric charge Q.

169
00:07:05,740 --> 00:07:08,740
Q stands for the electric charge.

170
00:07:08,740 --> 00:07:11,740
If we have an electric charge of a certain magnitude,

171
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:13,740
it creates around it an electric field.

172
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:15,740
You've all seen pictures of this,

173
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:18,740
the electric field spreads out away from the charge,

174
00:07:18,740 --> 00:07:23,740
very much like a fluid emanating from a,

175
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:26,740
from a pipe might spread out,

176
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:28,740
except it spreads out in three dimensions.

177
00:07:28,740 --> 00:07:32,740
That's the electric field created by a point charge.

178
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,740
Another example is if we have

179
00:07:34,740 --> 00:07:36,740
an electric current moving through a wire,

180
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,740
and electric currents are

181
00:07:38,740 --> 00:07:40,740
nothing but moving electric charges.

182
00:07:40,740 --> 00:07:43,740
Electric charges moving through a wire,

183
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:45,740
those electric charges,

184
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:48,740
their motion creates a magnetic field,

185
00:07:48,740 --> 00:07:51,740
and the magnetic field is a

186
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:54,740
field which circulates around the wire,

187
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:56,740
like that.

188
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:01,740
So these are examples of

189
00:08:01,740 --> 00:08:04,740
how charges and currents create fields.

190
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:06,740
What happens, for example,

191
00:08:06,740 --> 00:08:08,740
if you move the charge?

192
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:10,740
Supposing I suddenly move the charge

193
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:12,740
from one point to another point.

194
00:08:12,740 --> 00:08:15,740
Then the field has to rearrange itself.

195
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:19,740
Instead of pointing out of this point,

196
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:21,740
it will still point out of this point.

197
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:23,740
But it can't do that instantly.

198
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:25,740
Why not?

199
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:27,740
Because somebody out here is

200
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,740
not allowed to see an effect

201
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:34,740
before light could have been transmitted to this point.

202
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:37,240
So the field cannot suddenly

203
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:39,740
rearrange when you move a charge.

204
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:41,740
It rearranges

205
00:08:41,740 --> 00:08:43,740
by spreading out a wave.

206
00:08:43,740 --> 00:08:46,740
By spreading out a wave of rearrangement.

207
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:48,740
So that a little bit

208
00:08:48,740 --> 00:08:50,740
after the charge has been moved,

209
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:52,740
nearby the charge,

210
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,740
the field has been rearranged,

211
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:56,740
but far away,

212
00:08:56,740 --> 00:08:58,740
it's just as it was before.

213
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:00,740
And then as time goes on,

214
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:03,740
a wave spreads out, away from the charge,

215
00:09:03,740 --> 00:09:06,740
that signals the field far away

216
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:08,740
to rearrange, to accommodate the

217
00:09:08,740 --> 00:09:10,740
fact that the charge has moved.

218
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:14,740
If you move the charge back and forth,

219
00:09:14,740 --> 00:09:17,740
what will spread out is an electromagnetic wave.

220
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:20,740
If you vibrate the charge back and forth,

221
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:23,740
then what you will see going out

222
00:09:23,740 --> 00:09:25,740
is an electric and magnetic wave

223
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:29,740
that spreads out, just like a light wave, in fact.

224
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:31,740
That's what an antenna does.

225
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:34,740
An antenna simply moves charge back and forth like that.

226
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:37,740
The same thing is true of currents and wires.

227
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:40,740
If you suddenly reverse the current in a wire,

228
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:43,740
you would reverse the sign of the magnetic field.

229
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:46,740
Instead of the magnetic field circulating around this way,

230
00:09:46,740 --> 00:09:48,740
the magnetic field would circulate

231
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:50,740
around in the other direction.

232
00:09:50,740 --> 00:09:52,740
But that signal can't get very

233
00:09:52,740 --> 00:09:54,740
far in too short a time.

234
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:57,240
Einstein's rule was no signal ever

235
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,740
gets faster than the speed of light.

236
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:02,740
So it takes some time

237
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:05,740
for somebody far away to discover

238
00:10:05,740 --> 00:10:08,740
that the current has been reversed.

239
00:10:08,740 --> 00:10:10,740
That means that the magnetic field

240
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:12,740
the change in the magnetic field,

241
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:15,740
the fact that it's changed direction,

242
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,740
spreads out in a wave,

243
00:10:17,740 --> 00:10:19,740
and again, it's an electromagnetic wave.

244
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:22,740
And if you oscillate the charge back and forth,

245
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:24,740
if you oscillate the current back and forth,

246
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:26,740
you send out an electromagnetic wave.

247
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:28,740
That's the basic physics

248
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:30,740
that we want to describe

249
00:10:30,740 --> 00:10:34,740
by Maxwell's equations.

250
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:36,740
Before we do,

251
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:39,740
I want to do a little bit of review

252
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:41,740
from last time.

253
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:45,740
First, I just want to remind you about wave equations.

254
00:10:45,740 --> 00:10:48,740
Equations describing fields,

255
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:51,740
in this case, describing fields

256
00:10:51,740 --> 00:10:53,740
that can produce waves.

257
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:56,740
The first example, and we talked about it last time,

258
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:59,740
was a scalar field.

259
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:02,740
A field that doesn't have any indices mu and nu,

260
00:11:02,740 --> 00:11:04,240
but is just a single

261
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,740
number at each point in space.

262
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:07,740
Each point in space,

263
00:11:07,740 --> 00:11:09,740
there's a quantity,

264
00:11:09,740 --> 00:11:12,740
the field phi,

265
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:15,740
it depends on x and t,

266
00:11:17,740 --> 00:11:19,740
and it can vibrate, it can shake,

267
00:11:19,740 --> 00:11:21,740
it can do all sorts of things,

268
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:23,740
it can form wave fields.

269
00:11:23,740 --> 00:11:26,740
The last time, we discussed the kind of equation,

270
00:11:26,740 --> 00:11:29,740
the kind of wave equation that governs such fields,

271
00:11:29,740 --> 00:11:31,740
and I'll just remind you.

272
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:35,740
Remember what d mu is.

273
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:37,740
d mu stands for the derivative

274
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:39,740
with respect to the derivative.

275
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,740
d mu stands for the four directions of space-time,

276
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:43,740
x and t.

277
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:47,740
mu runs over four values,

278
00:11:47,740 --> 00:11:49,740
x, y, z, and t.

279
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:51,740
Incidentally, remember that x here

280
00:11:51,740 --> 00:11:56,740
really stands for x, y, and z.

281
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:58,740
Perhaps I shouldn't call it x,

282
00:11:58,740 --> 00:12:00,740
I'll call it x,

283
00:12:00,740 --> 00:12:02,740
well, let's continue to call it x.

284
00:12:02,740 --> 00:12:05,740
But it really stands for the four components of space,

285
00:12:05,740 --> 00:12:08,740
and also t stands for the time.

286
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:10,740
d by d mu means the derivative

287
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:12,740
with respect to any one of these,

288
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:17,740
so that's an ordinary derivative.

289
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:21,740
And we can differentiate phi.

290
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:23,740
A simple wave equation,

291
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:25,740
a very simple wave equation,

292
00:12:25,740 --> 00:12:27,240
would just say that the

293
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,740
derivative of a field is zero.

294
00:12:28,740 --> 00:12:31,740
That's not a very interesting wave equation,

295
00:12:31,740 --> 00:12:32,740
and the reason is,

296
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:35,740
what it says is the field is absolutely constant.

297
00:12:35,740 --> 00:12:37,740
If all of its derivatives,

298
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:38,740
the x and the y and

299
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:39,740
the z and the time derivative,

300
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,740
are zero,

301
00:12:40,740 --> 00:12:42,740
that means the field doesn't change at all,

302
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:43,740
with anything,

303
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:46,740
and so that's a very boring wave equation.

304
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:48,740
Completely boring.

305
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:50,740
A less boring equation

306
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:53,740
we get if we differentiate it again.

307
00:12:59,740 --> 00:13:01,740
I'm now using notation

308
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:03,740
that we described last time,

309
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:05,740
or several times in the past,

310
00:13:05,740 --> 00:13:07,740
where an upper interval,

311
00:13:07,740 --> 00:13:09,740
an upper interval,

312
00:13:09,740 --> 00:13:11,740
and a lower interval,

313
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:14,740
differ only by the sign of the time component.

314
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:17,740
So that this would really mean

315
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:22,740
the second derivative with respect to time

316
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:24,740
of a field,

317
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:27,740
minus the second derivative

318
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:30,740
with respect to x squared,

319
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:35,740
minus the second derivative with respect to y squared,

320
00:13:35,740 --> 00:13:37,740
minus the second derivative with respect to y squared,

321
00:13:37,740 --> 00:13:40,740
minus the second derivative with respect to z squared,

322
00:13:40,740 --> 00:13:42,740
is equal to zero.

323
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:44,740
Notice, as usual,

324
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,740
because I'm lazy,

325
00:13:46,740 --> 00:13:47,740
I've set the speed of light,

326
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:51,740
c, equal to one.

327
00:13:51,740 --> 00:13:52,740
You can go home,

328
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:53,740
and as an exercise,

329
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:55,240
figure out where the speeds

330
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:56,740
of light go into this equation.

331
00:13:56,740 --> 00:13:58,740
Alright, let's imagine now,

332
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:02,740
a wave moving down the z-axis.

333
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:04,740
A wave moving down the z-axis.

334
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:06,740
It's moving down the z-axis,

335
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:09,740
and that means phi only depends on z.

336
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:12,740
It doesn't depend on x and y.

337
00:14:12,740 --> 00:14:15,740
It may also depend on time.

338
00:14:15,740 --> 00:14:17,740
If a wave is moving,

339
00:14:17,740 --> 00:14:20,740
and you're standing still, watching it,

340
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:21,740
of course, you're going to watch it

341
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:22,740
go up and down and up and down,

342
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:24,740
so it will depend on time,

343
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:27,740
and it will also depend on z, where you are,

344
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:30,740
but it won't depend on the other directions.

345
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:32,740
So a wave moving down the z-axis,

346
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:35,740
we can completely ignore

347
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:37,740
these two terms,

348
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:39,740
which are the derivatives of phi

349
00:14:39,740 --> 00:14:41,740
in the direction in which it doesn't change.

350
00:14:41,740 --> 00:14:44,740
This is not there.

351
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:46,740
And our wave equation,

352
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:48,740
for a wave moving along z,

353
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:49,740
along the z-axis,

354
00:14:49,740 --> 00:14:53,740
sorry, this should be z, shouldn't it?

355
00:14:53,740 --> 00:14:56,740
It should equal zero.

356
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:59,740
What kind of solutions does such an equation have?

357
00:14:59,740 --> 00:15:01,740
We talked about it last time,

358
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:03,740
and there are two basic solutions

359
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:05,740
that this equation has.

360
00:15:05,740 --> 00:15:08,740
One of them is a function

361
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:11,740
of z plus t,

362
00:15:11,740 --> 00:15:16,740
and the other is a function of z minus t.

363
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:19,740
These are the two solutions

364
00:15:19,740 --> 00:15:22,740
which represent waves moving to the right

365
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:24,740
along the z-axis,

366
00:15:24,740 --> 00:15:26,740
and waves moving to the left.

367
00:15:26,740 --> 00:15:29,740
This one represents waves moving to the right

368
00:15:29,740 --> 00:15:31,740
along the positive z-axis.

369
00:15:31,740 --> 00:15:33,240
This one represents waves moving

370
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,740
along the left, to the left.

371
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:37,740
And the function of z is

372
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:38,740
any function,

373
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:39,740
any function,

374
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:41,740
any shaped wave profile,

375
00:15:41,740 --> 00:15:44,740
take any shaped wave profile at all,

376
00:15:44,740 --> 00:15:46,740
and allow it to just move

377
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:49,740
uniformly along the z-direction,

378
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,740
that constitutes a wave

379
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:53,740
moving down the z-axis

380
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:55,740
along the positive z-direction.

381
00:15:55,740 --> 00:15:58,740
That's a function of z minus t.

382
00:15:58,740 --> 00:16:00,740
If the wave moves in the other direction,

383
00:16:00,740 --> 00:16:04,740
then it's the same function of z plus t.

384
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:06,740
So that's the basic fact

385
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:09,740
that we learned last time about waves.

386
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:13,740
And there's one particular special kind of wave,

387
00:16:16,740 --> 00:16:18,740
the sine or cosine wave.

388
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:20,740
Let's just write it down

389
00:16:20,740 --> 00:16:22,740
for future reference.

390
00:16:22,740 --> 00:16:26,740
A wave which really has a wavy look to it,

391
00:16:26,740 --> 00:16:28,740
like this.

392
00:16:28,740 --> 00:16:30,740
Well, you can guess that's

393
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:32,740
either a sine or a cosine.

394
00:16:32,740 --> 00:16:33,740
And so, for example,

395
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:37,740
a wave of this type moving off to the right

396
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:40,740
would be a solution of the wave equation

397
00:16:40,740 --> 00:16:44,740
which has the form cosine

398
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:48,740
of z minus t.

399
00:16:48,740 --> 00:16:51,740
z minus t because it's moving to the right.

400
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:55,740
And furthermore, you can throw in a constant here,

401
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:57,740
usually called k, the wave number.

402
00:16:57,740 --> 00:16:59,740
Any constant.

403
00:16:59,740 --> 00:17:02,740
The bigger the constant is, incidentally,

404
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:05,740
the shorter the wavelength of the wave.

405
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:08,740
So if k is big, the wave looks like this.

406
00:17:08,740 --> 00:17:12,740
If k is small, the wave looks like this.

407
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:15,740
Those are the basic facts

408
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:17,740
that I want you to remember

409
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:19,740
about wave equations

410
00:17:19,740 --> 00:17:22,740
and, in particular, wave solutions.

411
00:17:22,740 --> 00:17:24,740
That they are functions of

412
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:26,740
z minus t, z plus t.

413
00:17:26,740 --> 00:17:28,740
They can have different wavelengths.

414
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:30,740
And they can be sines, cosines.

415
00:17:30,740 --> 00:17:31,740
And they move to the right,

416
00:17:31,740 --> 00:17:32,740
or they move to the left.

417
00:17:32,740 --> 00:17:34,740
That's it.

418
00:17:34,740 --> 00:17:36,740
That's what we need to know about waves.

419
00:17:38,740 --> 00:17:41,740
Before we go ahead with Maxwell's equations,

420
00:17:41,740 --> 00:17:43,740
just to remind you,

421
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:45,240
just to, since it's been a

422
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,740
week since we went through this,

423
00:17:46,740 --> 00:17:49,740
I will remind you of a little bit of mathematics.

424
00:17:49,740 --> 00:17:52,740
Elementary mathematics.

425
00:17:52,740 --> 00:17:55,240
First of all is the notion

426
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,740
of the cross product of two vectors.

427
00:17:57,740 --> 00:17:59,740
If we have any two vectors,

428
00:17:59,740 --> 00:18:01,740
these are ordinary vectors, not four vectors now,

429
00:18:02,740 --> 00:18:04,240
ordinary three-dimensional vectors

430
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,740
in three-dimensional space,

431
00:18:05,740 --> 00:18:08,740
then we have the cross product,

432
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:11,740
b dot a,

433
00:18:11,740 --> 00:18:14,740
b cross a, excuse me,

434
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:16,740
the cross product of two vectors.

435
00:18:16,740 --> 00:18:20,740
The cross product is itself another vector.

436
00:18:20,740 --> 00:18:22,740
If we have two vectors,

437
00:18:22,740 --> 00:18:25,740
each pointing in some direction with a given length,

438
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:28,740
we can multiply them together

439
00:18:28,740 --> 00:18:30,740
and make another vector.

440
00:18:30,740 --> 00:18:34,740
The cross product is defined by its components.

441
00:18:34,740 --> 00:18:36,740
So for example, the x component

442
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:38,740
of b cross a is defined,

443
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:40,740
this is definition,

444
00:18:40,740 --> 00:18:43,740
is defined to be

445
00:18:43,740 --> 00:18:50,740
by times ax minus bx times ay.

446
00:18:50,740 --> 00:18:54,740
And now if you want to find the other components,

447
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:58,740
you just cycle through x, y, and z.

448
00:18:58,740 --> 00:19:00,740
So for example,

449
00:19:00,740 --> 00:19:04,740
b cross a, the y component,

450
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:06,740
you go x to y,

451
00:19:06,740 --> 00:19:08,740
equals b,

452
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:10,740
well, y goes to z,

453
00:19:10,740 --> 00:19:13,740
x goes to y,

454
00:19:13,740 --> 00:19:15,740
the root is x to y, y to z,

455
00:19:15,740 --> 00:19:17,740
z back to x.

456
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:18,740
b goes to z,

457
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:20,740
sorry, y goes to z,

458
00:19:20,740 --> 00:19:21,740
x goes to y,

459
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:24,740
minus b, y,

460
00:19:24,740 --> 00:19:26,740
x goes to y,

461
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:28,740
a goes to z.

462
00:19:28,740 --> 00:19:29,740
And likewise for the last,

463
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:32,740
I'm doing this once, I won't do it again.

464
00:19:32,740 --> 00:19:34,740
b cross a,

465
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:36,740
z component of it,

466
00:19:36,740 --> 00:19:38,740
is equal to

467
00:19:38,740 --> 00:19:39,740
x, y, the next,

468
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:43,740
y, z, the next one must be x, b, x,

469
00:19:43,740 --> 00:19:47,740
x, y, the next one must be z,

470
00:19:47,740 --> 00:19:51,740
minus b, z, a, x.

471
00:19:51,740 --> 00:19:53,740
These are definitions.

472
00:19:53,740 --> 00:19:55,740
These are definitions of the

473
00:19:55,740 --> 00:19:57,740
cross product between two vectors.

474
00:19:57,740 --> 00:20:00,740
Notice that the cross product itself has components,

475
00:20:00,740 --> 00:20:03,740
and so it must be a vector.

476
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:04,740
Okay?

477
00:20:04,740 --> 00:20:07,240
Now, another way of multiplying two

478
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,740
vectors together is the dot product.

479
00:20:09,740 --> 00:20:11,740
The dot product,

480
00:20:13,740 --> 00:20:16,740
the dot product of two vectors

481
00:20:16,740 --> 00:20:19,740
is a scalar,

482
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:23,740
a dot b, and it only has one component.

483
00:20:23,740 --> 00:20:25,740
It's the same in every reference frame,

484
00:20:25,740 --> 00:20:26,740
or the same

485
00:20:26,740 --> 00:20:28,740
when you rotate the reference frame.

486
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:32,740
And its definition is a, x, b, x,

487
00:20:32,740 --> 00:20:35,740
plus a, y, b, y,

488
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:38,740
plus a, z, b, z.

489
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:40,740
Can that be read? I hope that can be read.

490
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:43,740
a, x, b, x, plus

491
00:20:43,740 --> 00:20:46,740
a, y, b, y, plus a, z, b, z.

492
00:20:46,740 --> 00:20:48,740
That's the dot product,

493
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:50,740
and it's a scalar.

494
00:20:50,740 --> 00:20:54,740
That's one set of concepts that,

495
00:20:54,740 --> 00:20:56,740
that we've been through several times.

496
00:20:56,740 --> 00:20:59,740
Now the other set of concepts

497
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:03,740
are the curl of a vector

498
00:21:03,740 --> 00:21:05,740
and the divergence of a vector.

499
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:08,740
And here's the way you think about them.

500
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:11,740
They're built up out of derivatives

501
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:13,740
of the components of the vector.

502
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:16,740
Partial derivatives with respect to x, y, and z.

503
00:21:16,740 --> 00:21:19,740
All you have to imagine in your head

504
00:21:19,740 --> 00:21:22,740
is that derivative with respect to x,

505
00:21:22,740 --> 00:21:24,740
and derivative with respect to y,

506
00:21:24,740 --> 00:21:26,740
and derivative with respect to y,

507
00:21:26,740 --> 00:21:28,740
and derivative with respect to z,

508
00:21:28,740 --> 00:21:30,740
pretend that those symbols

509
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:33,740
are the three components of a vector.

510
00:21:33,740 --> 00:21:34,740
They're not.

511
00:21:34,740 --> 00:21:36,740
They're the three components of a derivative.

512
00:21:36,740 --> 00:21:38,740
But just pretend that they're

513
00:21:38,740 --> 00:21:40,740
the three components of a vector.

514
00:21:40,740 --> 00:21:46,740
And now, imagine del cross a vector a.

515
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:48,740
What does that mean?

516
00:21:48,740 --> 00:21:50,740
It's something that's made up out of the derivatives

517
00:21:50,740 --> 00:21:52,740
of the components of a,

518
00:21:52,740 --> 00:21:55,740
but, oh, I'm sorry,

519
00:21:55,740 --> 00:22:00,740
the three components are called the vector del.

520
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:09,740
Del is just a shorthand for upside down triangle.

521
00:22:11,740 --> 00:22:13,740
Del cross a. How do you make it?

522
00:22:13,740 --> 00:22:15,740
Well, you just go back to this formula,

523
00:22:15,740 --> 00:22:18,740
and wherever you saw a stick in,

524
00:22:18,740 --> 00:22:20,740
either d by dx, d

525
00:22:20,740 --> 00:22:22,740
by dy, or d by dz.

526
00:22:22,740 --> 00:22:25,740
So the curl of a is then just,

527
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:34,740
well, we have a, so that's d by dx.

528
00:22:34,740 --> 00:22:36,740
I should have called this b, shouldn't I?

529
00:22:36,740 --> 00:22:38,740
It would have made more sense

530
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:41,740
and been nicer if I would have called this b.

531
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:45,740
All right.

532
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:46,740
So instead of a,

533
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:49,740
we write the three components of the derivative.

534
00:22:49,740 --> 00:22:52,740
Wherever we see b, we just stick b.

535
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:54,740
So that's bx,

536
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:57,740
and we're going to do the curl.

537
00:22:57,740 --> 00:22:59,740
We're doing the curl.

538
00:22:59,740 --> 00:23:01,740
Slow down.

539
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:03,740
We're doing the curl.

540
00:23:03,740 --> 00:23:05,740
The curl is over here.

541
00:23:05,740 --> 00:23:08,740
The x component of the curl,

542
00:23:08,740 --> 00:23:10,740
del cross b,

543
00:23:10,740 --> 00:23:12,740
the x component of it,

544
00:23:12,740 --> 00:23:14,740
all right, that's this.

545
00:23:14,740 --> 00:23:16,740
All right.

546
00:23:16,740 --> 00:23:19,740
So it's ax by,

547
00:23:19,740 --> 00:23:23,740
well, that's d by dx by,

548
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:26,740
d by dy,

549
00:23:26,740 --> 00:23:31,740
minus d by dy bx.

550
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:33,740
We can go through it and cycle through it

551
00:23:33,740 --> 00:23:37,740
and find the other components of the curl of b,

552
00:23:37,740 --> 00:23:38,740
but they're always made up,

553
00:23:38,740 --> 00:23:41,740
d by dy, d by dy.

554
00:23:41,740 --> 00:23:43,740
They're always made up of

555
00:23:43,740 --> 00:23:45,740
derivatives of the components of b

556
00:23:45,740 --> 00:23:46,740
in the same pattern,

557
00:23:46,740 --> 00:23:48,740
in the same exact pattern that

558
00:23:48,740 --> 00:23:50,740
the cross product is made up.

559
00:23:50,740 --> 00:23:51,740
What about del dot b?

560
00:23:51,740 --> 00:23:53,740
That's called the divergence of b.

561
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:56,740
Del dot b,

562
00:23:56,740 --> 00:23:59,740
well, we come to the definition of the divergence

563
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:01,740
of the dot product.

564
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:03,740
Ax times bx,

565
00:24:03,740 --> 00:24:06,740
that will be d by dx,

566
00:24:06,740 --> 00:24:08,740
bx,

567
00:24:08,740 --> 00:24:10,740
plus d by dy,

568
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:12,740
by,

569
00:24:12,740 --> 00:24:14,740
plus d by dz,

570
00:24:14,740 --> 00:24:17,740
bz.

571
00:24:17,740 --> 00:24:20,740
Now, these two objects,

572
00:24:20,740 --> 00:24:23,740
they're composed out of derivatives of the components

573
00:24:23,740 --> 00:24:25,740
of vectors.

574
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:27,740
If a vector is constant in space,

575
00:24:27,740 --> 00:24:30,740
if it's a vector field which is constant in space,

576
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:35,740
it has neither a divergence nor a curl.

577
00:24:35,740 --> 00:24:37,740
Roughly speaking,

578
00:24:37,740 --> 00:24:40,740
a vector has a divergence

579
00:24:40,740 --> 00:24:42,740
when it seems to be emanating,

580
00:24:42,740 --> 00:24:44,740
a vector field has a divergence

581
00:24:44,740 --> 00:24:46,740
when it seems to be emanating out of some place,

582
00:24:46,740 --> 00:24:48,740
like this.

583
00:24:48,740 --> 00:24:50,740
A vector has a curl

584
00:24:50,740 --> 00:24:52,740
when it seems to,

585
00:24:53,740 --> 00:24:57,740
curl around some place.

586
00:24:57,740 --> 00:25:00,740
So if we had a magnetic field, for example,

587
00:25:00,740 --> 00:25:04,740
in a wire that was going into the blackboard,

588
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:07,740
that vector would have a curl.

589
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:10,740
If we have an electric charge

590
00:25:10,740 --> 00:25:12,740
giving rise to an electric field

591
00:25:12,740 --> 00:25:14,740
pointing out from some point,

592
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:17,740
that field would have a divergence.

593
00:25:17,740 --> 00:25:19,740
We've gone through these things before,

594
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:20,740
these are not new,

595
00:25:20,740 --> 00:25:22,740
just reminding you of them.

596
00:25:23,740 --> 00:25:26,740
And now I want to write down Maxwell's equations

597
00:25:26,740 --> 00:25:29,740
in terms of these objects.

598
00:25:31,740 --> 00:25:33,740
Our goal is going to be to write Maxwell's equations,

599
00:25:33,740 --> 00:25:35,740
that's easy,

600
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:37,740
you can get them off somebody's t-shirt,

601
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:40,740
lots and lots of t-shirts with Maxwell's equations on them.

602
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:42,740
But then to understand in what sense

603
00:25:42,740 --> 00:25:45,740
they are the same in every reference frame.

604
00:25:45,740 --> 00:25:47,740
That's our goal,

605
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:48,740
to see that Maxwell's equations

606
00:25:48,740 --> 00:25:49,740
can be written in a form

607
00:25:49,740 --> 00:25:51,740
which is the same in every reference frame.

608
00:25:53,740 --> 00:25:56,740
Alright, so let me write them down.

609
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:02,740
Curl of the electric field,

610
00:26:02,740 --> 00:26:05,740
of the electric field, you construct its curl,

611
00:26:07,740 --> 00:26:10,740
is equal to minus

612
00:26:10,740 --> 00:26:14,740
the time derivative of the magnetic field.

613
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:17,740
That's Maxwell equation number one.

614
00:26:17,740 --> 00:26:20,740
Maxwell equation number two,

615
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:23,740
divergence of the magnetic field,

616
00:26:23,740 --> 00:26:25,740
is equal to zero.

617
00:26:25,740 --> 00:26:28,740
All that says,

618
00:26:28,740 --> 00:26:32,740
